       <div id="hashing" class="sub__menu"><b>Hashing:</b></div>
             <p class="copy__block-left-medium-large black__font">            

Hash algorithms are used widely in bitcoin and KPcoin and you could say that hashing puts the "crypto" in "cryptocurrency"!  Hashing has some almost magical properties which make it very useful when trying to secure data - particularly in a situation where that data is available to a network of people who don't know each other, and don't trust each other.
<br>
<br>
The most important hashing technique used in the bitcoin protocol is SHA256 which stands for Secure Hashing Algorithm 256-bit. The easiest way to understand it to play with it:
                 
